***Plot 1-*** Trinidad and Tabago have the Highest Sexual Violence Stats and the Impact of this on GDP & Inflation

-   I decided to focus more on African countries/Countries who have large populations that descend from Africa such as Trinidad and Tabago. After analysising the Datasets I found that Trinidad and Tabago had the highest observed value in relation to sexual violence against women (24.8) which can also be seen in the Time-Series Chart.
-   In the following paragraph I will discuss the implications of Sexual Violence has had on Trinidad and Tabagos GDP. In the graph below Trinidad & Tabagos GDP does not have a positive relationship with the indicator. There GDP has decreased significantly since Covid-19 which correlates to the discovers of increase violence against women due to the pandemic (insert reference). Due to an increase in violence In the National Women's Health Survey for Trinidad and Tobago(2018). The IADB study found that between 1.6 and 2 % of Gross National Product was forgone in womens wages because of domestic violence. In the 2005 IADB study of how sexual violence effects GDP in Trinidad & Tabago it estimated that sexual abuse and domestic violence cost the country a sizeable \$487.7 million or a little more than 0.5% of GDP for that year. In analyzing the burden of costs, the study showed it is evident that the victim of violence accounts for \$244.3 million or 0.26% of GDP. Further analysis shows that the government bears the next highest burden of the cost,\$80.6 million or 0.08% of GDP with the community following closely with a cost burden of \$71.8 million or 0.07% of GDP in 2005.(Theodore, et.al, IADB)


