***Plot 2-*** Senegal has the Lowest Sexual Violence Stats and the Impact of this on GDP & Inflation

-   According to the UN Indicator Dataset, Senegal had the lowest observed value of women who have experienced sexual violence between the ages of 18-29. However, Senegal's economic growth stood at 4.8% of gross domestic product (GDP), 1.3 percentage points below the estimated economic growth rate of 6.1% for 2021. Inflation, which reached its highest point in decades, was estimated at 8.5% on average in 2022, compared with 2.2% in 2021 -- almost 3 times the maximum limit of 3% set within the West African Economic and Monetary Union.(UNICEF,2022) Which can be seen in the data plot below. However, it must be noted that Senegal has a high rate of sexual violence in regards to children (those under the age of 18), particularly sexual violence, as it is estimated around 15,000 girls ages 15-17 are victims of sexual violence.(UNICEF Senegal,2022) And thus the data does not take into account the impacts of sexual violenece on younger ages in relation to GDP,Inflation etc. 

